snippet.title: Pet animals songs for kindergarten | Pet animals songs for kids
snippet.description:
Lest sing the animals songs for kids!
Cat, hamster and the dog. Lets sing!

This nice and warm animal song is the manifestation of all children’s dreams.

Each time we want them to do something at home, they start thinking how fascinating life would be if they were pets: cats, dogs or hamsters...they wouldn’t have to do all the homework or housework…

My children are the same...the song is my answer to their ideas. It’s a kind of the  other side, which apparently our kids don’t take into account when dreaming.
If your child tells you that he or she would like to be a cat when you ask him or her to take the rubbish out, you can sing that song as the answer….



Oh, I’d like to be a pet
silky, sweety little cat.
I could play with a ball
or sleep all day long
 I’d like to be a cat.

Or, I’d like to be a dog
cute and fluffy little dog.
I could bark  very loud
hide and seek with you outside.
Oh, I’d like to be a dog.

Hamsters’ life is pretty nice
they can ride merry-go-round.
Hamster-that’s what I should be
how to change, tell me please.
Cause I’d like to be a pet.

But you couldn’t ride a bike
or play cards with your mama and dad.
Pets are pretty and they’re funny
but I love my awesome sonny.
Come and hug and don’t be sad.

snippet.title: Ravan Ek Mahayodha - Marathi Mythology Movie For Kids
snippet.description:
Ravan Ek Mahayoddha - Marathi
Ravan Ek Mahayoddha is 2009 animated movie based on one of the most famous mythological characters - Ravan. The Music is by Devjeet Roy. In this movie the Ramayan is narrated from Ravan's perspective. Ravan Ek Mahayoddha narrates the tale of the valiant, intelligent and brave King of Lanka - Ravan. Ravan's birth name was Dasahanan and he always wanted to be the king of the three worlds so that everyone could worship him. An ardent devotee of Lord Shiva, he received ten heads as per the boon from Lord Brahma. However, Ravan met his nemesis and death in the form of Lord Rama, an incarnation of Lord Vishnu, after he abducted Rama's wife Sita. Watch the epic battle of good vs evil.
